---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '~/components/CTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Fuel retail — KKT"
  description="Optimus operates price, margin, and operations across fuel networks. Live at Alfa Oil — 600+ stations."
  ogImage="/og/fuel-retail.png"
>
  <article class="prose-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Industries — Fuel retail</div>
      <h1 class="h1-page">For fuel networks.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Optimus is our operating system for fuel retail — pricing, margin
        steering, and station-level operations under one roof. Live in
        production; not a pilot.
      </p>

      <section class="ind-pullquote">
        <blockquote>
          <p>
            Margin becomes a controlled variable, not an outcome.
            Stockouts surface days before they happen, when there is
            still time to act.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section class="proof-strip">
        <div class="proof-card">
          <div class="proof-num">600+</div>
          <div class="proof-label">stations operating Optimus</div>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-card">
          <div class="proof-num">$500M</div>
          <div class="proof-label">network revenue at Alfa Oil</div>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-card">
          <div class="proof-num">11</div>
          <div class="proof-label">fuel types, multi-region</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="cta-row">
        <a href="/solutions/optimus" class="btn-primary">See Optimus →</a>
        <a href="/case-studies/alfa-oil" class="btn-ghost">Read the Alfa Oil case</a>
      </section>

      <section class="starts">
        <div class="section-label">Engagement starting points</div>
        <h2 class="h2-section">Where fuel-network engagements typically begin.</h2>
        <p class="starts-lede">
          Optimus is the operating engine. Around it, we usually pick up
          one or two of these as the first concrete shipping
          workstream — driven by what the diagnostic surfaces.
        </p>

        <div class="starts-grid">
          <div class="start-card">
            <h3 class="start-title">Procurement and replenishment intelligence.</h3>
            <p>
              The Optimus core. Stockout forecasting, supplier
              consolidation, working capital release. The thing the
              head of supply opens at 8 AM.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="start-card">
            <h3 class="start-title">Pricing posture.</h3>
            <p>
              Network-level pricing decisions in a daily cadence,
              with margin posture explicit. What happens when margin
              becomes a controlled variable rather than an outcome.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="start-card">
            <h3 class="start-title">Station-level operations.</h3>
            <p>
              Per-station fill levels, fuel mix, conflict resolution,
              audit trails. The visibility under the network number,
              where most operational money is actually moved.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="start-card">
            <h3 class="start-title">Working capital and turnover.</h3>
            <p>
              $ frozen in inventory and where to release it, per
              fuel and per region. Inventory turnover stops being a
              quarterly review.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="starts-tail">
          See the full surface on
          <a href="/solutions/optimus">Optimus</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="cdn-preview">
        <div class="cdn-tag">Cost of doing nothing &middot; Phase 1.5</div>
        <h3 class="cdn-title">Quantify the gap to top-quartile peers.</h3>
        <p>
          A single-page calculator: 6–8 inputs, three quantified gap
          scenarios (conservative / median / aggressive), every number
          with a source. Currently in benchmark calibration. The
          methodology is already public.
        </p>
        <a href="/methods/cost-of-doing-nothing" class="cdn-link">Read the methodology →</a>
      </section>
    </div>

    <CTA
      heading="Fuel network diagnostic, two weeks."
      body="A scoped look at where Optimus applies to your network — pricing posture, margin posture, station-level operations, and what shipping looks like."
    />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-page { padding-top: clamp(40px, 6vh, 72px); }
  .section-label { margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .h1-page {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 48px);
    line-height: 1.16;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: clamp(17px, 2vw, 20px);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .ind-pullquote {
    margin: 8px 0 40px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    background: var(--surface-alt);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .ind-pullquote blockquote { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .ind-pullquote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.6vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 32ch;
  }

  .proof-strip {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
    max-width: 820px;
  }
  .proof-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
  }
  .proof-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 32px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .proof-label {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .starts {
    margin-top: 32px;
    padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .starts .section-label { margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .starts h2 { margin-bottom: 18px; max-width: 26ch; }
  .starts-lede {
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .starts-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .starts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  .start-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 22px 24px;
  }
  .start-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .start-card p { font-size: 15px; max-width: 50ch; }
  .starts-tail {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .starts-tail a {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .starts-tail a:hover { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; text-decoration-color: var(--accent); }

  .cdn-preview {
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding: 26px 28px;
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .cdn-tag {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .cdn-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }
  .cdn-preview p {
    font-size: 14px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .cdn-link {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .cdn-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
